{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861873273,"sessionID":"ses_286676b49ffeNnKh1BK4ix0sgt","part":{"id":"prt_d79990140001nnMLs90K6tXpeD","messageID":"msg_d7998e373001ViBKJc3I5n2X1T","sessionID":"ses_286676b49ffeNnKh1BK4ix0sgt","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full scope. The existing design.md only covers AR-020 (pack command). I need to write a comprehensive design.md for AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider that covers the entire CLI toolkit, client-go library, and Python SDK based on the detailed specifications provided.","time":{"start":1775861873269,"end":1775861873269}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861873283,"sessionID":"ses_286676b49ffeNnKh1BK4ix0sgt","part":{"id":"prt_d79990681001pUZ1PgF0DwYqGx","messageID":"msg_d7998e373001ViBKJc3I5n2X1T","sessionID":"ses_286676b49ffeNnKh1BK4ix0sgt","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_d1cebcf32eda42f1ad64266b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-026: K8s/AgentCube Provider — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThe K8s/AgentCube Provider delivers a complete developer toolchain for AI agent lifecycle management on Kubernetes. It consists of three components:\n\n1. **CLI Toolkit** (`kubectl-agentcube`) — Command-line interface for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube CRDs or standard Kubernetes deployments.\n2. **Client-Go Library** — Generated Kubernetes typed client for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources in group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`.\n3. **Python SDK** (`agentcube-sdk`) — High-level Python client library for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 System Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          Developer Workstation                           │\n│                                                                          │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  CLI Toolkit     │  │   Python SDK     │  │    client-go (Go)     │  │\n│  │  (Typer/Python)  │  │  (requests)      │  │  (k8s.io/client-go)   │  │\n│  │                  │  │                  │  │                       │  │\n│  │  pack/build/     │  │  CodeInterpreter │  │  AgentRuntime         │  │\n│  │  publish/invoke/ │  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  CodeInterpreter      │  │\n│  │  status          │  │  clients         │  │  typed clients        │  │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘  └────────┬─────────┘  └───────────┬───────────┘  │\n│           │                     │                        │              │\n└───────────┼─────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────┘\n            │                     │                        │\n            ▼                     ▼                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Kubernetes Cluster                                │\n│                                                                          │\n│  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  AgentRuntime CRD   │    │  Standard K8s Resources               │   │\n│  │  (volcano.sh)       │    │                                       │   │\n│  │                     │    │  Deployment + NodePort Service        │   │\n│  │  AgentRuntime       │    │  (provider=k8s mode)                  │   │\n│  │  CodeInterpreter    │    │                                       │   │\n│  └──────────┬──────────┘    └───────────────────┬───────────────────┘   │\n│             │                                   │                       │\n│             ▼                                   ▼                       │\n│  ┌─────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  Workload Manager   │    │  Router                               │   │\n│  │  (Control Plane)    │    │  (Data Plane)                         │   │\n│  │                     │    │                                       │   │\n│  │  Session creation   │    │  /v1/namespaces/{ns}/                 │   │\n│  │  Session deletion   │    │    agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/ │   │\n│  │                     │    │    code-interpreters/{name}/invoc/    │   │\n│  └─────────────────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.3 Component Relationships\n\n```\nCLI Toolkit\n├── Runtime Layer (orchestration)\n│   ├── PackRuntime     → validates workspace, generates Dockerfile, saves metadata\n│   ├── BuildRuntime    → builds container images (local Docker or cloud)\n│   ├── PublishRuntime  → deploys to K8s (AgentRuntime CR or Deployment+Service)\n│   ├── InvokeRuntime   → POSTs to agent endpoint with session management\n│   └── StatusRuntime   → reads and displays agent status\n│\n├── Service Layer (infrastructure)\n│   ├── MetadataService    → load/save/validate agent_metadata.yaml\n│   ├── DockerService      → Docker SDK operations (build, push, login, remove)\n│   ├── KubernetesProvider → standard K8s Deployment + Service management\n│   └── AgentCubeProvider  → AgentRuntime CRD management via CustomObjects API\n│\n└── Model Layer (data structures)\n    ├── AgentMetadata      → Pydantic model for agent configuration\n    └── MetadataOptions    → dataclass for CLI option parsing\n\nPython SDK\n├── High-Level Clients\n│   ├── CodeInterpreterClient → context manager, session lifecycle, file/command ops\n│   └── AgentRuntimeClient    → context manager, invoke with session bootstrap\n│\n├── Low-Level Clients\n│   ├── ControlPlaneClient          → Workload Manager HTTP (create/delete session)\n│   ├── CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient → Router HTTP (execute, files)\n│   └── AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient    → Router HTTP (invoke)\n│\n└── Utilities\n    ├── http.py      → create_session (requests.Session with HTTPAdapter)\n    ├── utils.py     → read_token_from_file (SA token)\n    └── log.py       → get_logger\n\nclient-go\n├── Clientset          → versioned.Interface, RuntimeV1alpha1()\n├── Typed Clients      → AgentRuntimeInterface, CodeInterpreterInterface\n├── Informers          → SharedInformerFactory, per-type informers\n├── Listers            → AgentRuntimeLister, CodeInterpreterLister\n└── Fake Clients       → in-memory test doubles\n```\n\n### 1.4 Package Layouts\n\n#### CLI Toolkit (`cmd/cli/`)\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Project metadata, dependencies, entry points\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, exports: app, PackRuntime, BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n│   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, all commands, _handle_error, version_callback\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports runtimes + MetadataOptions\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            — PackRuntime\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py           — BuildRuntime\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         — PublishRuntime\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          — InvokeRuntime\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py          — StatusRuntime\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py                — Placeholder module docstring (no symbols)\n└── examples/\n    ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n    └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n```\n\n#### Python SDK (`sdk-python/`)\n\n```\nsdk-python/\n├── pyproject.toml                     — Package agentcube-sdk, dependencies\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    — Public exports: CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── code_interpreter.py            — CodeInterpreterClient\n│   ├── agent_runtime.py               — AgentRuntimeClient\n│   ├── exceptions.py                  — Exception classes\n│   ├── clients/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports client classes\n│   │   ├── control_plane.py           — ControlPlaneClient\n│   │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n│   │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    — AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── __init__.py                — Empty (module marker)\n│       ├── http.py                    — create_session\n│       ├── utils.py                   — read_token_from_file\n│       └── log.py                     — get_logger\n```\n\n#### client-go (`client-go/`)\n\n```\nclient-go/\n├── clientset/\n│   └── versioned/\n│       ├── clientset.go               — Clientset, Interface, constructors\n│       ├── scheme/\n│       │   ├── register.go            — Scheme / codecs\n│       │   └── doc.go\n│       ├── fake/\n│       │   ├── clientset_generated.go — Fake clientset\n│       │   ├── register.go\n│       │   └── doc.go\n│       └── typed/runtime/v1alpha1/\n│           ├── runtime_client.go      — RuntimeV1alpha1Client, Interface\n│           ├── agentruntime.go        — AgentRuntimeInterface\n│           ├── codeinterpreter.go     — CodeInterpreterInterface\n│           ├── generated_expansion.go — Expansion interfaces\n│           ├── doc.go\n│           └── fake/\n│               ├── fake_runtime_client.go\n│               ├── fake_agentruntime.go\n│               ├── fake_codeinterpreter.go\n│               └── doc.go\n├── informers/\n│   └── externalversions/\n│       ├── factory.go                 — SharedInformerFactory\n│       ├── generic.go                 — GenericInformer, ForResource\n│       ├── internalinterfaces/\n│       │   └── factory_interfaces.go  — NewInformerFunc, TweakListOptionsFunc\n│       └── runtime/\n│           ├── interface.go           — Group accessor\n│           └── v1alpha1/\n│               ├── interface.go       — v1alpha1 accessors\n│               ├── agentruntime.go    — AgentRuntime informer\n│               └── codeinterpreter.go — CodeInterpreter informer\n└── listers/\n    └── runtime/v1alpha1/\n        ├── agentruntime.go            — AgentRuntimeLister\n        ├── codeinterpreter.go         — CodeInterpreterLister\n        └── expansion_generated.go\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n#### CLI Toolkit\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump |\n| `httpx` | `>=0.24.0` | Async HTTP for invoke |\n| `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python |\n| `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, tables, colored output |\n| `packaging` | `>=23.0` | Version detection |\n| `importlib-resources` | `>=6.0.0` | Template access |\n| `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Semantic version handling |\n| `kubernetes` | `>=28.0.0` | K8s client (optional, k8s extra) |\n\n#### Python SDK\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | — | HTTP client |\n| `PyJWT` | `>=2.0.0` | JWT handling |\n| `cryptography` | — | Crypto primitives |\n\n#### client-go\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|---------|\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | `v0.34.1` | Kubernetes Go client |\n| `k8s.io/code-generator` | `v0.34.1` | Code generation |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 AgentMetadata (Pydantic BaseModel)\n\nCanonical metadata model persisted as `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Description |\n|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | (required) | Unique name identifying the agent |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Programming language used |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | (required) | Command to launch the agent |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Port exposed by the agent runtime |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string for publishing |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image information |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication configuration |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for image publishing |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Workload Manager |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | URL for the Router |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Path for the readiness probe |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port for the readiness probe |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The session ID for the agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment information |\n\n**Validators:**\n- `validate_language` → must be in `['python', 'java']` (lowercased)\n- `validate_build_mode` → must be in `['local', 'cloud']` (lowercased)\n- `validate_port` → must be in range `1..65535`\n\n### 2.2 MetadataOptions (dataclass)\n\nCLI option parsing intermediate structure.\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n\n**Classmethod:** `from_options(cls, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"MetadataOptions\"`\n\n### 2.3 Runtime Classes\n\n#### PackRuntime\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def pack(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _validate_workspace_structure(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _load_or_create_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _apply_option_overrides(self, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def _validate_language_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_python_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_java_compatibility(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _process_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _process_python_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _process_java_dependencies(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _generate_dockerfile(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Optional[Path]: ...\n    def _generate_python_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    def _generate_java_dockerfile(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> str: ...\n    def _update_pack_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, dockerfile_path: Optional[Path]) -> None: ...\n    def _prepare_output_path(self, workspace_path: Path, output_path: Optional[str]) -> Path: ...\n    def _infer_entrypoint(self, workspace_path: Path, language: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n#### BuildRuntime\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def build(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _increment_version(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_build_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> None: ...\n    def _build_local(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _build_cloud(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _update_build_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, build_result: Dict[str, str], tag: str = \"latest\") -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### PublishRuntime\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n    def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### InvokeRuntime\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, workspace_path: Path, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(self, workspace_path: Path) -> Tuple[Any, str, str]: ...\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(self, agent_id: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], endpoint: str, workspace_path: Path) -> Any: ...\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(self, endpoint: str, payload: Dict[str, Any], headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]], workspace_path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n**Known issue:** `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; if false, `return response` raises `UnboundLocalError`.\n\n#### StatusRuntime\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n```\n\n### 2.4 Service Classes\n\n#### DockerService\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n    def build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str: ...\n    def push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n    def _docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None: ...\n    def _tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None: ...\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool: ...\n```\n\n#### MetadataService\n\n```python\nclass MetadataService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    def load_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def save_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def update_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, updates: Dict[str, Any]) -> AgentMetadata: ...\n    def validate_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path) -> bool: ...\n    def _validate_python_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n    def _validate_java_workspace(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### KubernetesProvider\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, replicas: int = 1, node_port: Optional[int] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _create_deployment(self, name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str], replicas: int, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _create_service(self, name: str, port: int, node_port: Optional[int]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None: ...\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n```\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False, kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None) -> None: ...\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(self, agent_name: str, image_url: str, port: int, entrypoint: Optional[str] = None, env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None, readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str: ...\n    def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n```\n\n**CR API:** `group=\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`, `version=\"v1alpha1\"`, `plural=\"agentruntimes\"`.\n\n### 2.5 Python SDK Clients\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", ttl: int = 3600, workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None, router_url: Optional[str] = None, auth_token: Optional[str] = None, verbose: bool = False, session_id: Optional[str] = None): ...\n    def _init_data_plane(self) -> None: ...\n    def __enter__(self): ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n    def stop(self) -> None: ...\n    def execute_command(self, command: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\"): ...\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(self, agent_name: str, namespace: str = \"default\", router_url: Optional[str] = None, verbose: bool = False, session_id: Optional[str] = None, timeout: int = 120, connect_timeout: float = 5.0): ...\n    def __enter__(self): ...\n    def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n    def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n### 2.6 Exception Hierarchy (Python SDK)\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n### 2.7 client-go Types\n\n#### AgentRuntime CRD\n\n- **Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- **Version:** `v1alpha1`\n- **Plural:** `agentruntimes`\n- **Kind:** `AgentRuntime`\n\n#### Clientset Interface\n\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeInterface\n\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {\n    Create(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.CreateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Update(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, opts metav1.UpdateOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.DeleteOptions) error\n    DeleteCollection(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.DeleteOptions, listOpts metav1.ListOptions) error\n    Get(ctx context.Context, name string, opts metav1.GetOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    List(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    Watch(ctx context.Context, opts metav1.ListOptions) (watch.Interface, error)\n    Patch(ctx context.Context, name string, pt types.PatchType, data []byte, opts metav1.PatchOptions, subresources ...string) (*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimeExpansion\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 CLI Commands\n\n#### Console Script Entry Point\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n```\n\nTyper app: `app = typer.Typer(name=\"agentcube\", help=\"...\", no_args_is_help=True, rich_markup_mode=\"rich\", add_completion=False)`.\n\n#### Root Callback\n\n```python\ndef main(\n    version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", help=\"Show version and exit\", callback=version_callback, is_eager=True),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\", help=\"Enable verbose output\"),\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Behaviors:**\n- `--version`: prints `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup), exits via `typer.Exit()`\n- `--verbose`/`-v`: calls `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n\n#### pack Command\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--agent-name` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the agent name |\n| `--language` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Programming language (python, java) |\n| `--entrypoint` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override the entrypoint command |\n| `--port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Port to expose in the Dockerfile |\n| `--build-mode` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Build strategy: local or cloud |\n| `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for packaged workspace |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**Success output:**\n```\n✓ Agent 'my-agent' packaged successfully!\n  Workspace: /path/to/workspace\n  Metadata:  /path/to/workspace/agent_metadata.yaml\n```\n\n**Error handling:** prints `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red; if verbose, prints traceback; exits with code `1`.\n\n#### build Command\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--proxy` | `-p` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom proxy URL for dependency resolution |\n| `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--output` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Output path for build artifacts |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**Behaviors:**\n- Local build: requires Docker running; raises `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` if unavailable\n- Version increment: bumps `metadata.version` (patch for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1`, or fallback `{version}-1`); reverts on build failure\n- Tag derived from metadata version\n\n#### publish Command\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--version` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n| `--image-url` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n| `--image-username` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n| `--image-password` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n| `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n| `--region` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n| `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n| `--node-port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort to use (30000-32767) for K8s deployment |\n| `--replicas` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n| `--namespace` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**AgentCube provider prerequisites:** metadata must contain `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`; otherwise raises `ValueError`.\n\n**Standard K8s publish flow:** calls `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updates metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure raises `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata.\n\n#### invoke Command\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--payload` | — | `str` | `\"{}\"` | JSON-formatted input passed to the agent |\n| `--header` | — | `Optional[List[str]]` | `None` | Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Repeatable. |\n| `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**Behaviors:**\n- Invalid JSON payload: prints error in red, exits with code `1`\n- Invalid header format (no single `:` separator): prints expected `key:value` format, exits with code `1`\n- Session header: if metadata contains `session_id`, adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header\n- AgentRuntime CR URL rewrite: when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`, rewrites URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n#### status Command\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n| `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) |\n| `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**Behaviors:**\n- Displays status in Rich `Table`\n- If `status == \"not_published\"` (no `agent_id`): prints guidance to publish first, exits with code `1`\n- If `status == \"error\"`: exits with code `1`\n\n### 3.2 Metadata File Format\n\n**Primary filename:** `agent_metadata.yaml`  \n**Load fallbacks:** `agent.yaml` → `metadata.yaml`\n\n**Save format:**\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nlanguage: python\nentrypoint: python main.py\nport: 8080\nbuild_mode: local\n# ... other fields, None values excluded\n```\n\nWritten with `yaml.dump(default_flow_style=False, indent=2, sort_keys=False)` after `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`.\n\n### 3.3 Workspace Validation Rules\n\n| Language | Requirement | Error if Missing |\n|----------|-------------|------------------|\n| Any | Directory exists | `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` |\n| Python | At least one `*.py` file in workspace root | `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` |\n| Java | `pom.xml` in workspace root | `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` |\n\n### 3.4 Dockerfile Generation\n\n**When generated:** If no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace root.\n\n**Python Dockerfile template:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM python:3.10-slim\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\nCOPY . .\nEXPOSE {port}\nCMD {entrypoint}\n```\n\n**Java Dockerfile template:**\n```dockerfile\nFROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17 AS build\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY pom.xml .\nRUN mvn dependency:go-offline\nCOPY src ./src\nRUN mvn package -DskipTests\n\nFROM eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine\nWORKDIR /app\nCOPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar\nEXPOSE {port}\nCMD {entrypoint}\n```\n\n### 3.5 Docker Integration\n\n| Operation | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `build_image` | Tags `{image_name}:{tag}`, passes optional `buildargs` from proxy settings, returns `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time` |\n| `push_image` | Logs in if username+password provided, retags when needed, streams push logs, returns `pushed_image` and `push_time` |\n| `remove_image` | Returns `True` on success; logs warning and returns `False` on failure |\n| `check_docker_available` | Returns `True` if Docker daemon is running and accessible |\n\n### 3.6 Kubernetes — Standard Provider\n\n| Operation | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `deploy_agent` | Creates/patches Deployment + NodePort Service; returns `deployment_name`, `service_name`, `namespace`, `replicas`, `container_port`, `node_port`, `service_url` as `http://localhost:{node_port}` |\n| `wait_for_deployment_ready` | Polls until ready or timeout (default 120s); raises `TimeoutError` on expiry |\n| `delete_agent` | Deletes Deployment + Service; ignores 404 on individual deletes; returns `{\"status\": \"deleted\", \"deployment_name\", \"namespace\"}` |\n| `get_agent_status` | Returns pod status, replica counts, conditions |\n\n### 3.7 Kubernetes — AgentCube AgentRuntime CR\n\n| Operation | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `deploy_agent_runtime` | Creates/patches AgentRuntime CR; embeds `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / `ROUTER_URL` from params or env when missing in `env_vars`; sets `sessionTimeout` to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`; references `imagePullSecrets` `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]` |\n| `get_agent_runtime` | Returns CR object or `None` if not found |\n\n### 3.8 Python SDK — Code Interpreter\n\n#### Control Plane HTTP\n\n| Method | Path | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| `POST` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n| `DELETE` | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success in `delete_session` |\n\n**Headers:**\n- `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n- `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n\n#### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) — Base URL\n\nIf `base_url` is not provided:\n```text\nbase_path = \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### Data Plane — HTTP (relative to `self.base_url`)\n\n| Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n|--------|---------------|---------------|\n| `POST` | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n| `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n| `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download (`clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`) |\n| `GET` | `api/files` | query `path` |\n\n**Headers:**\n- Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json` when `body` is set\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only (no JSON Content-Type)\n\n### 3.9 Python SDK — Agent Runtime\n\n#### Data Plane — Base URL\n\n```text\nbase_path = f\"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\"\nself.base_url = urljoin(router_url, base_path)\n```\n\n#### Data Plane — HTTP\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| `GET` | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | — |\n| `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n**Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is the method argument or `self.timeout` (default 120).\n\n### 3.10 Configuration Resolution\n\n#### CLI Toolkit\n\n| Component | Resolved settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `KubernetesProvider` | `namespace` ← arg or `\"default\"`; `kubeconfig` ← arg or `$KUBECONFIG` or `~/.kube/config` |\n| `AgentCubeProvider` | Same as KubernetesProvider |\n| `DockerService` | Uses `docker.from_env()` (respects `$DOCKER_HOST`, `$DOCKER_CERT_PATH`) |\n\n#### Python SDK\n\n| Component | Resolved settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ← `workload_manager_url` or `$WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ← `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `$ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient`; `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`, `session_id` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | `router_url` ← arg or `$ROUTER_URL`; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` passed to data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Same timeout defaults as above |\n\n### 3.11 Entrypoint Inference\n\n| Language | Inference Logic |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Python | Find first `*.py` file in workspace root (alphabetically sorted); default to `python <file>` |\n| Java | Default to `java -jar app.jar` |\n\nIf inference fails and no `--entrypoint` provided: raise `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")`.\n\n### 3.12 Dependency Processing\n\n| Language | Detection | Action |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Python | `requirements.txt` exists | Validate file is readable; set `requirements_file` in metadata |\n| Python | `requirements.txt` missing | Create empty file in workspace |\n| Java | `pom.xml` exists | Validate XML is parseable |\n| Java | `pom.xml` missing | Already caught by workspace validation |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 CLI Error Handling Pattern\n\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n**Key behaviors:**\n- All subcommand exceptions flow through `_handle_error`\n- Subcommand's local `--verbose` flag controls traceback display (independent of global `-v`)\n- Exit code is always `1` on error\n\n### 4.2 Sentinel Errors (CLI Toolkit)\n\n#### PackRuntime\n\n| Error | Condition |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")` | Workspace path doesn't exist |\n| `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")` | Python language, no `*.py` files |\n| `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found in Java workspace\")` | Java language, no `pom.xml` |\n| `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")` | Language not in `['python', 'java']` |\n| `ValueError(\"Entrypoint is required but could not be inferred\")` | No entrypoint and inference failed |\n| `RuntimeError(\"Failed to generate Dockerfile: {reason}\")` | Dockerfile generation failure |\n\n#### BuildRuntime\n\n| Error | Condition |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` | Docker daemon unavailable in local build mode |\n\n#### PublishRuntime\n\n| Error | Condition |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `ValueError` (message requiring `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`) | AgentCube provider, metadata lacks required URLs |\n| `RuntimeError` (after recording error in metadata) | Deployment readiness check failed |\n\n#### InvokeRuntime\n\n| Error | Condition |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `json.JSONDecodeError` | Invalid payload JSON |\n| `ValueError` (expected `key:value` format) | Invalid header format |\n| `UnboundLocalError` (known bug) | `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with non-HTTP endpoint |\n\n#### StatusRuntime\n\n| Error | Condition |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `typer.Exit(1)` | Status is `not_published` or `error` |\n\n### 4.3 Python SDK Error Handling\n\n| Exception | Raised When |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `ValueError` | Router URL missing, session_id not initialized, missing response header |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Remote command returns non-zero exit code |\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base class for all SDK errors |\n| `SessionError` | Session creation or management failure (defined, not currently raised) |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Data plane operation failure (defined, not currently raised) |\n| `requests` exceptions | Network-level failures |\n\n#### Context Manager Cleanup\n\n**CodeInterpreterClient:**\n- `__exit__` calls `stop()` → closes data-plane session, deletes control-plane session if `session_id` was set, closes control plane HTTP session\n- Data plane init failure after session create: logs warning, calls `delete_session(session_id)`, sets `session_id` to `None`, re-raises\n\n**AgentRuntimeClient:**\n- `__exit__` calls `close()` → closes underlying `requests.Session`\n\n### 4.4 Timeout Behavior\n\n| Component | Default Read Timeout | Default Connect Timeout |\n|-----------|---------------------|------------------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 120s | 5.0s |\n| `execute_command` | `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds (buffer to avoid ReadTimeout before PicoD returns exit 124) | 5.0s |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 CLI Toolkit Tests\n\n#### PackRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_pack_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPackRuntime_ValidPythonWorkspace` | Valid Python workspace with `main.py` → packs successfully |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ValidJavaWorkspace` | Valid Java workspace with `pom.xml` → packs successfully |\n| `TestPackRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoPythonFiles` | Python language, no `*.py` → `ValueError(\"No Python files found\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoPomXml` | Java language, no `pom.xml` → `ValueError(\"pom.xml not found\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_UnsupportedLanguage` | `language=ruby` → `ValueError(\"Unsupported language\")` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ExistingMetadata` | `agent_metadata.yaml` present → loads and merges |\n| `TestPackRuntime_FallbackMetadata` | Only `agent.yaml` present → loads from fallback |\n| `TestPackRuntime_NoMetadata` | No metadata files → creates new from options |\n| `TestPackRuntime_CliOverrides` | CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointPython` | No entrypoint, Python workspace → infers `python main.py` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointJava` | No entrypoint, Java workspace → infers `java -jar app.jar` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_InferEntrypointFails` | No `*.py` files, no entrypoint → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPackRuntime_GeneratePythonDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Python → generates correct Dockerfile |\n| `TestPackRuntime_GenerateJavaDockerfile` | No Dockerfile, Java → generates correct Dockerfile |\n| `TestPackRuntime_ExistingDockerfile` | Dockerfile exists → not regenerated |\n| `TestPackRuntime_CreateRequirementsTxt` | Python workspace without `requirements.txt` → creates empty file |\n| `TestPackRuntime_OutputPath` | `--output` specified → returns output path, not workspace |\n| `TestPackRuntime_MetadataSavedCorrectly` | Metadata file written with correct YAML format |\n| `TestPackRuntime_PortValidation` | `--port=0` → Pydantic validation error |\n| `TestPackRuntime_PortValidationHigh` | `--port=70000` → Pydantic validation error |\n\n#### BuildRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_build_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestBuildRuntime_LocalBuildSuccess` | Local Docker build succeeds |\n| `TestBuildRuntime_DockerUnavailable` | Docker unavailable → `RuntimeError` |\n| `TestBuildRuntime_VersionIncrement` | Version bumped on successful build |\n| `TestBuildRuntime_VersionRevertOnFailure` | Version reverted on build failure |\n| `TestBuildRuntime_CloudBuild` | Cloud build mode delegates correctly |\n| `TestBuildRuntime_ProxySettings` | Proxy passed as build args |\n\n#### PublishRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestPublishRuntime_AgentCubeProvider` | Publish to AgentRuntime CR |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_K8sProvider` | Publish to Deployment + Service |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_MissingUrls` | AgentCube provider without required URLs → `ValueError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_ReadinessTimeout` | Deployment not ready → `RuntimeError` |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_LocalImagePrep` | Prepare local image for publishing |\n| `TestPublishRuntime_CloudImagePrep` | Prepare cloud image for publishing |\n\n#### InvokeRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_invoke_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_ValidPayload` | Valid JSON payload → successful invoke |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_InvalidPayload` | Invalid JSON → error, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_InvalidHeader` | Bad header format → error, exit 1 |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_SessionHeader` | `session_id` in metadata → `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header added |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_AgentCubeUrlRewrite` | AgentRuntime CR → URL rewritten to invocation path |\n| `TestInvokeRuntime_DirectHttpInvocation` | Standard K8s → direct POST to endpoint |\n\n#### StatusRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_status_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestStatusRuntime_NotPublished` | No `agent_id` → guidance to publish, exit 1 |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_CrStatus` | AgentRuntime CR status read from `cr_object[\"status\"]` |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_K8sStatus` | Standard K8s deployment status |\n| `TestStatusRuntime_ErrorStatus` | Error status → exit 1 |\n\n#### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_commands.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestCli_VersionFlag` | `--version` → prints version, exits |\n| `TestCli_VerboseLogging` | `-v` → DEBUG logging enabled |\n| `TestCli_PackCommand` | `pack` command integration |\n| `TestCli_BuildCommand` | `build` command integration |\n| `TestCli_PublishCommand` | `publish` command integration |\n| `TestCli_InvokeCommand` | `invoke` command integration |\n| `TestCli_StatusCommand` | `status` command integration |\n| `TestCli_HandleErrorVerbose` | Error + verbose → traceback printed |\n| `TestCli_HandleErrorQuiet` | Error, no verbose → message only |\n\n#### MetadataService Tests (`tests/services/test_metadata_service.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestMetadataService_SaveAndLoad` | Save → load round-trip preserves fields |\n| `TestMetadataService_FallbackLoad` | `agent.yaml` present, `agent_metadata.yaml` absent → loads fallback |\n| `TestMetadataService_ExcludeNone` | `None` fields excluded from YAML output |\n| `TestMetadataService_YamlFormat` | Output uses `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, `default_flow_style=False` |\n| `TestMetadataService_ValidatePythonWorkspace` | Python workspace validation |\n| `TestMetadataService_ValidateJavaWorkspace` | Java workspace validation |\n\n#### DockerService Tests (`tests/services/test_docker_service.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestDockerService_BuildImage` | Build image with tag and build args |\n| `TestDockerService_PushImage` | Push with login and retag |\n| `TestDockerService_RemoveImage` | Remove image success and failure |\n| `TestDockerService_CheckAvailable` | Docker availability check |\n\n#### KubernetesProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestK8sProvider_DeployAgent` | Deploy Deployment + Service |\n| `TestK8sProvider_WaitForReady` | Wait for deployment ready |\n| `TestK8sProvider_WaitTimeout` | Timeout exceeded → `TimeoutError` |\n| `TestK8sProvider_DeleteAgent` | Delete agent, ignore 404 |\n| `TestK8sProvider_GetStatus` | Get agent status |\n| `TestK8sProvider_SanitizeName` | Name sanitization |\n\n#### AgentCubeProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_DeployRuntime` | Deploy AgentRuntime CR |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_EnvVarInjection` | WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL / ROUTER_URL from env |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_SessionTimeouts` | sessionTimeout=15m, maxSessionDuration=8h |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_GetRuntime` | Get AgentRuntime CR |\n| `TestAgentCubeProvider_SanitizeName` | Name sanitization |\n\n### 5.2 Python SDK Tests\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient Tests (`tests/test_code_interpreter.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_ContextManager` | Context manager cleanup calls `stop()` |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_DataPlaneInitFailure` | Data plane init failure → cleanup session, re-raise |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_RouterUrlRequired` | No router URL → `ValueError` |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_ExecuteCommand` | Execute command, parse response |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_CommandFailure` | Non-zero exit → `CommandExecutionError` |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_RunCode` | Python code execution path (write file + execute) |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_WriteFile` | Write file via data plane |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_UploadFile` | Multipart upload |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_DownloadFile` | Stream download |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterClient_ListFiles` | List files in path |\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient Tests (`tests/test_agent_runtime.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_ContextManager` | Context manager cleanup calls `close()` |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_BootstrapSession` | GET invocation URL, read `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_MissingSessionHeader` | Header missing → `ValueError` |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeWithoutSession` | No session_id → `ValueError` |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_Invoke` | POST JSON payload with session header |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeClient_InvokeTimeout` | Timeout tuple `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient Tests (`tests/clients/test_control_plane.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_CreateSession` | POST session, return `sessionId` |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_CreateSessionMissingId` | Response without `sessionId` → `ValueError` |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_DeleteSession` | DELETE session, 404 → success |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_DeleteSessionFailure` | Other failure → log, return `False` |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_AuthToken` | SA token file resolution |\n| `TestControlPlaneClient_EnvVarUrl` | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var |\n\n#### DataPlaneClient Tests (`tests/clients/test_data_plane.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestCodeInterpreterDataPlane_ExecuteCommand` | POST `api/execute` with timeout buffer |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterDataPlane_WriteFile` | POST `api/files` with base64 content |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterDataPlane_UploadFile` | Multipart POST `api/files` |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterDataPlane_DownloadFile` | GET `api/files/{path}` with stream |\n| `TestCodeInterpreterDataPlane_ListFiles` | GET `api/files` with query |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeDataPlane_Invoke` | POST JSON with session header |\n| `TestAgentRuntimeDataPlane_BootstrapSession` | GET base URL, read session header |\n\n#### Exception Tests (`tests/test_exceptions.py`)\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestExceptions_CommandExecutionError` | Exit code, stderr, command attributes |\n| `TestExceptions_AgentCubeError` | Base exception class |\n| `TestExceptions_SessionError` | Defined for extension |\n| `TestExceptions_DataPlaneError` | Defined for extension |\n\n### 5.3 client-go Tests\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `TestClientset_NewForConfig` | Clientset creation from rest.Config |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_Create` | Create AgentRuntime CR |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_Get` | Get AgentRuntime by name |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_List` | List AgentRuntimes in namespace |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_Update` | Update AgentRuntime |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_Delete` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| `TestAgentRuntime_Watch` | Watch AgentRuntime changes |\n| `TestCodeInterpreter_Create` | Create CodeInterpreter CR |\n| `TestFakeClientset` | Fake clientset CRUD operations |\n| `TestInformer_AgentRuntime` | AgentRuntime informer events |\n| `TestLister_AgentRuntime` | AgentRuntimeLister Get/List |\n\n### 5.4 Test Helpers\n\n```python\n@pytest.fixture\ndef python_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef java_workspace(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n    ws = tmp_path / \"java-agent\"\n    ws.mkdir()\n    (ws / \"pom.xml\").write_text(\"<project>...</project>\\n\")\n    (ws / \"src\").mkdir()\n    return ws\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef workspace_with_metadata(python_workspace: Path) -> Path:\n    metadata = python_workspace / \"agent_metadata.yaml\"\n    metadata.write_text(\"agent_name: test-agent\\nlanguage: python\\nentrypoint: python main.py\\nport: 8080\\nbuild_mode: local\\n\")\n    return python_workspace\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_docker_client(mocker):\n    client = mocker.patch(\"docker.from_env\")\n    client.return_value.ping.return_value = True\n    return client.return_value\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef mock_k8s_config(mocker):\n    mocker.patch(\"kubernetes.config.load_kube_config\")\n    mocker.patch(\"kubernetes.client.AppsV1Api\")\n    mocker.patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\")\n    mocker.patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\")\n```\n\n### 5.5 Mock Strategy\n\n| Component | Mock Approach |\n|-----------|---------------|\n| Filesystem | `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces |\n| MetadataService | Real instance (lightweight, no external deps) |\n| DockerService | Mock `docker.from_env()` and client methods |\n| Kubernetes | Mock `kubernetes.client.*` APIs or use fake client-go |\n| HTTP (SDK) | `httpx-mock` / `requests-mock` for control/data plane |\n| Console output | `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)` |\n| Time | `freezegun` for timeout/version tests |\n\n### 5.6 Gate Requirements\n\n1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n5. `go test ./client-go/...` all pass\n6. All Runtime public methods have unit tests\n7. Error paths tested (invalid workspace, missing files, bad language, network failures)\n8. Integration tests for CLI → Runtime → Service flow\n\n---\n\n## 6. Deployment Considerations\n\n### 6.1 CLI Toolkit\n\n1. **Workspace Path Resolution:** The `--workspace` path is resolved to absolute via `Path.resolve()` before any operations. Relative paths are supported but normalized.\n\n2. **Metadata File Location:** Always written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`. If the workspace is read-only, pack will fail with a permission error.\n\n3. **Dockerfile Generation:** Only generated if no `Dockerfile` exists. Custom Dockerfiles are preserved. The generated Dockerfile uses fixed base images (`python:3.10-slim`, `maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17`) — users needing different versions must provide their own.\n\n4. **Requirements File:** For Python workspaces without `requirements.txt`, an empty file is created. This ensures the generated Dockerfile's `COPY requirements.txt` step succeeds.\n\n5. **Output Path:** When `--output` is specified, the metadata is still saved to the original workspace, not the output directory. The output path is returned for downstream use.\n\n6. **Language Validation:** Pydantic validators enforce `language ∈ {python, java}` and `build_mode ∈ {local, cloud}` at the metadata level. CLI-level validation is not performed; errors surface during metadata construction.\n\n7. **Kubernetes Access:** Both `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` require a valid kubeconfig. Resolution order: `kubeconfig` argument → `$KUBECONFIG` env var → `~/.kube/config`.\n\n8. **Docker Access:** `DockerService` uses `docker.from_env()` which respects `$DOCKER_HOST`, `$DOCKER_CERT_PATH`, and `$DOCKER_TLS_VERIFY`.\n\n### 6.2 Python SDK\n\n1. **Router URL Required:** Both `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` require `router_url` (argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var). No default is provided.\n\n2. **Authentication:** `ControlPlaneClient` resolves auth token from `auth_token` argument or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` (in-cluster SA token). If present, sets `Authorization: Bearer {token}`.\n\n3. **Session Management:** Sessions are created on first use (if `session_id` not provided) and cleaned up on context manager exit. Data plane init failure triggers session cleanup.\n\n4. **Header Naming:** SDK uses lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` for all Router requests. CLI uses `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (different casing) — this is a potential integration inconsistency.\n\n5. **Timeout Buffer:** `execute_command` adds 2.0 seconds to the read timeout to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124.\n\n### 6.3 client-go\n\n1. **Code Generation:** Run `make gen-client` → `hack/update-codegen.sh` with `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1, `--with-watch` flag, output package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`.\n\n2. **Expansion Interfaces:** `AgentRuntimeExpansion` and `CodeInterpreterExpansion` are empty — reserved for custom methods.\n\n3. **Fake Clients:** Full fake clientset available for unit testing without a real K8s cluster.\n\n4. **Informers:** `SharedInformerFactory` supports namespace filtering, custom resync, and list options tweaking.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Implementation Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Foundation (Day 1-2)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n2. Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model\n3. Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options()` classmethod\n4. Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata`, `save_metadata`, `update_metadata`\n5. Write model and metadata service tests\n\n### Phase 2: Pack Runtime (Day 3-4)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` with `PackRuntime` class\n2. Implement workspace validation, language compatibility checks\n3. Implement metadata loading/creation with fallback logic\n4. Implement option overrides and entrypoint inference\n5. Implement Dockerfile generation for Python and Java\n6. Implement dependency processing\n7. Write comprehensive PackRuntime tests\n\n### Phase 3: Build Runtime (Day 5-6)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` with `BuildRuntime` class\n2. Create `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` with `DockerService` class\n3. Implement Docker availability check, image build, push, remove\n4. Implement version increment logic with rollback on failure\n5. Implement local and cloud build modes\n6. Write BuildRuntime and DockerService tests\n\n### Phase 4: Publish Runtime (Day 7-8)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` with `PublishRuntime` class\n2. Create `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` with `KubernetesProvider` class\n3. Create `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` with `AgentCubeProvider` class\n4. Implement standard K8s Deployment + Service creation\n5. Implement AgentRuntime CR creation with env var injection\n6. Implement image preparation (local and cloud)\n7. Implement deployment readiness waiting\n8. Write PublishRuntime and provider tests\n\n### Phase 5: Invoke & Status Runtime (Day 9-10)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` with `InvokeRuntime` class\n2. Create `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` with `StatusRuntime` class\n3. Implement payload validation, header parsing, session header injection\n4. Implement AgentCube URL rewrite for AgentRuntime CR\n5. Implement status display with Rich Table\n6. Write InvokeRuntime and StatusRuntime tests\n\n### Phase 6: CLI Integration (Day 11-12)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/cli/main.py` with Typer app and all commands\n2. Wire `version_callback`, `_handle_error`, root callback\n3. Implement all command handlers with Rich Progress spinners\n4. Create `agentcube/__init__.py` with exports\n5. Create `pyproject.toml` with dependencies and entry points\n6. Write CLI command integration tests\n\n### Phase 7: Python SDK (Day 13-15)\n\n1. Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` with exception hierarchy\n2. Create `agentcube/utils/` with `http.py`, `utils.py`, `log.py`\n3. Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` with `ControlPlaneClient`\n4. Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` with `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`\n5. Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` with `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n6. Create `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` with `CodeInterpreterClient`\n7. Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` with `AgentRuntimeClient`\n8. Write comprehensive SDK tests\n\n### Phase 8: client-go (Day 16-17)\n\n1. Define CRD types in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n2. Run `make gen-client` to generate clientset, informers, listers\n3. Verify fake clients and expansion interfaces\n4. Write client-go tests\n\n### Phase 9: Integration & Polish (Day 18-20)\n\n1. Run full test suite across all components\n2. Fix gaps, improve coverage to ≥ 80%\n3. Run `ruff check`, `mypy`, `go vet`\n4. End-to-end integration tests (pack → build → publish → invoke → status)\n5. Documentation updates\n\n---\n\n## 8. Known Issues and Limitations\n\n### 8.1 Known Bugs\n\n| Issue | Component | Description | Severity |\n|-------|-----------|-------------|----------|\n| UnboundLocalError | InvokeRuntime | `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` only assigns `response` inside `if endpoint.startswith(\"http\"):`; non-HTTP endpoint causes `UnboundLocalError` on `return response` | P1 |\n| Header casing mismatch | CLI vs SDK | CLI uses `X-Agentcube-Session-Id`, SDK uses `x-agentcube-session-id` — potential Router incompatibility | P2 |\n\n### 8.2 Limitations\n\n| Limitation | Component | Description |\n|------------|-----------|-------------|\n| Language support | CLI Toolkit | Only `python` and `java` languages supported |\n| Dockerfile templates | CLI Toolkit | Fixed base image versions; no customization via CLI |\n| Entrypoint inference | CLI Toolkit | Python picks first `*.py` alphabetically; may not be correct main file |\n| Entrypoint validation | CLI Toolkit | No validation that inferred entrypoint actually runs |\n| Metadata output path | CLI Toolkit | Metadata saved to original workspace even when `--output` specified |\n| Atomicity | CLI Toolkit | No atomicity guarantee; partial files may remain on failure |\n| SessionError/DataPlaneError | Python SDK | Defined but not raised by core client modules |\n| Authorization on data plane | Python SDK | Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Future Changes\n\n| Change | Component | Description | Priority |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|----------|\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Support for Node.js/Go workspaces | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Custom Dockerfile templates from config | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Multi-stage build optimization for Python (uv/pip-tools) | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Workspace archive output (tar.gz) for cloud build mode | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Pre-pack hook for custom validation scripts | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | Python SDK | Raise `SessionError` / `DataPlaneError` in appropriate paths | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Python SDK | Retry logic for transient network failures | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | Python SDK | Async support for data plane operations | P3 |\n| AR-0XX | client-go | Custom methods in expansion interfaces | P2 |\n| AR-0XX | All | Unified header naming convention (lowercase) | P1 |\n| AR-0XX | CLI Toolkit | Fix `UnboundLocalError` in `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` | P1 |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/